\par \pard 
\par Defend is an option usually only used when in a Party, however, if a player is experienced enough, they can use Defend when running through a room right before a monster strikes.  Defend will increase a characters Defense (while selected) by 50% during combat.  For more information on commands during combat, see the \uldb Commands\plain\fs20  section of this Helplesson.
\par 
\par It is in combat that your character gains the most experience.  The tougher the monster, the more experience your character will gain.
\par \pard 
\par Sometimes, your character may become "pinned\'94.  This means that your character cannot learn any more (gain experience) until they reach the next level in their current guild.  It also means that your character has enough experience to make level and is 1 experience point away from making the next level.  This quite often happens when a character is looking for a quested monster.  The only way to become "un-pinned\'94 is to make a level.
