\pard\keepn \plain\b\fs28 Location Spells\plain\fs24 
\par \pard 
\par \fs20 Created by the Mage\'92s guild for failed attempts at movement, spells of this nature are able to locate other specified characters or objects, and aid the caster in  orientation when  lost.
\par \fs24 
\par \pard\li175 \b\fs20 Set Sanctuary\tab 
\par \plain\fs20 Base Level: 1\tab Guilds: Nom, War, Pal, Nin, Vil, See, Thi, Sca, Mag, Sor, Wiz, Hea
\par Required Stats: NONE\tab 
\par \i NON-COMBAT Spell, will set the "Sanctuary\'94 return location.
\par \plain\fs20 Casting this spell will set the caster\'92s "Sanctuary\'94 location.  This means that when the caster  casts Sanctuary,  he or she will then be returned to the exact location where Set Sanctuary was last cast.\fs24 
\par \fs20 
\par \b Depth Perception\tab 
\par \plain\fs20 Base Level: 3\tab Guilds: See, Mag, Wiz
\par \pard\li175 Required Stats: 13 Int, 13 Wis, 13 Con\tab 
\par \i NON-COMBAT Spell, informs the caster of what level they are on.
\par \plain\fs20 Useful in helping  lost explorers \'91find themselves\'92.
\par \tab  
\par \b Soul Search\tab 
\par \plain\fs20 Base Level: 6\tab Guilds: See, Mag, Wiz
\par Required Stats: 15 Int, 14 Wis, 12 Dex\tab 
\par \i NON-COMBAT Spell, will seek out and return the location of another character.
\par \plain\fs20 This spell allows the caster to search for another character.  The caster will receive the offset coordinates, \b relative to the spell caster\plain\fs20 , of where the searched soul is (if they are on the same level).  If the character being searched for is not on the same level as the caster, an up or down value will be returned.
\par \pard\li175  \tab  
\par \b Find Direction\tab 
\par \plain\fs20 Base Level: 6\tab Guilds: See, Mag, Wiz
\par Required Stats: 14 Int, 14 Wis, 14 Con\tab 
\par \i NON-COMBAT Spell, informs the caster of what direction they are facing.
\par \plain\fs20 Also useful in helping  lost explorers \'91find themselves\'92.
\par  
