\pard\keepn \plain\b\fs28 Main Menu\plain\fs24 
\par \pard 
\par \fs20 The first thing you see when you start Mordor will be the Main Menu. In order to play the game, you must first Create or Load a character, and then Run the character.
\par 
\par Below is a brief summary of each available option on the Main Menu.
\par \fs24 
\par \pard\li175 \b\fs20\cf1 Create Character
\par \plain\fs20 This option is only available when another character is not loaded.  Clicking this button will bring up the Character Creation window, allowing a new character to be created.  If the new character is saved, it will automatically be loaded when you come back to the Main Menu.  All you then need to do is Run the character.
\par 
\par \b\cf1 Run Character
\par \plain\fs20 When you Load a character, the Create Character button will be replaced with Run Character.  This will start the game with the currently loaded character (specified in the caption of the command button).
\par \pard\li175 
\par \b\cf1 Change Password
\par \plain\fs20 This option allows you to change the password for the currently loaded character.  Passwords are important since they protect your characters from somebody else having access to them.  This feature also allows more than one person to play on a single machine.
\par 
\par \b\cf1 Exchange Items
\par \plain\fs20 This option allows you to exchange gold and items between two characters that are at the same location.  This is extremely useful when a player wants to keep a "bank\'94 character - that is: a character that just sits in the City (or Dungeon) and holds items.  This is also the only way one can exchange items or gold with a dead character.
\par \pard\li175 
\par \b\cf1 Load Character
\par \plain\fs20 Will prompt the user for the character to Load, then load the character (if the proper password is specified).
\par 
\par \b\cf1 Unload Character
\par \plain\fs20 Will unload the currently loaded character, allowing the user to Create or Load another character.
\par 
\par \b\cf1 Character List
\par \plain\fs20 This option will list all available characters on the current Machine.
\par 
\par \i\b Some of the options listed above will remain unavailable (invisible) until a character is loaded.
\par \plain\fs24 
\par \b\fs20\cf1 Options\plain\fs24 
\par \pard\li175 \fs20 This will bring up the Game Options Window, which is described in the next section.
\par \fs24 
\par \b\fs20\cf1 Hall of Records\plain\fs24 
\par \fs20 This will bring up a list of characters that hold the set Records for various abilities in the game.
\par \fs24 
\par \b\fs20\cf1 About\plain\fs24 
\par \fs20 This option displays the current information and credits for Mordor.
\par 
\par \b\cf1 Helplesson
\par \plain\fs20 Executes this Helplesson
\par 
\par \b\cf1 Exit
\par \plain\fs20 Shuts down Mordor and returns to the Program Manager.\fs24 
