\b\fs28 Visual Spells\plain\fs24 
\par \pard 
\par \fs20 In a collected effort, the Sorcerer\'92s and Wizard\'92s guilds managed to create spells that allowed one to turn invisible to the naked eye, and allowed one to see those who were invisible as well.
\par \fs24 
\par \pard\li175 \b\fs20 Sight Veil\tab 
\par \plain\fs20 Base Level: 2\tab Guilds: See (6), Mag (4), Sor, Wiz (8)
\par Required Stats: 12 Int, 12 Wis, 12 Cha\tab 
\par \i NON-COMBAT Spell, will cause the receiving character to become Invisible.
\par \plain\fs20 This spell is very useful defensive spell.  When cast the recipient becomes invisible to the naked eye, only those with special abilities will be able to see the character.
\par  \tab  
\par \b See Invisible\tab 
\par \plain\fs20 Base Level: 2\tab Guilds: See (6), Mag (4), Sor, Wiz (8)
\par Required Stats: 12 Int, 12 Wis, 12 Cha\tab 
\par \pard\li175 \i NON-COMBAT Spell, will cause the receiving character to see Invisible.
\par \plain\fs20 This spell will enable a character to see those who are invisible to the naked eye.
\par  \tab  
\par \b Mass Sight Veil\tab 
\par \plain\fs20 Base Level: 8\tab Guilds: Sor
\par Required Stats: 10 Str, 12 Int, 16 Wis, 10 Cha, 10 Dex\tab 
\par \i NON-COMBAT Spell, will cause the entire party to become Invisible.
\par \plain\fs20 This spell is the same as Sight Veil except that it affects the entire party.
